  "text": "In the present study, we observed negative association of BMI with free T3 and free T4 and weak positive correlation with TSH. In a study in Germany, euthyroid subjects with TSH in the upper normal range (2.5-4.5 mU/L) were more obese (BMI > 30 Kg/m 2 ), had higher triglyceride levels, and an increased likelihood of having metabolic syndrome [CITATION_1] .",
